## 📋 Requirements

### 💻 Software Requirements
- Python 3.x  
- IDE / Code Editor (VS Code / PyCharm / Jupyter Notebook)  

---

### 📚 Python Libraries
- numpy (for calculations)  
- matplotlib (for visualization)  
- time (for simulation delays)  
- tkinter / pygame (optional, for GUI simulation)  

---

### ⚙️ System Requirements
- Laptop / PC with Python installed  
- Basic understanding of Python programming  
- Internet (optional, for installing libraries)  

---

### 🧠 Simulation Requirements
- Logic for train detection (distance/time-based simulation)  
- Gate control logic (open/close mechanism)  
- Event handling for train approach and departure  
- Visualization or GUI (optional for better demonstration)  

---

### 🌐 Optional Enhancements
- Real-time visualization dashboard  
- Sensor-based integration (IoT version)  
- Machine learning for train prediction  
- Integration with hardware (ESP32 / Arduino)  
